
[Richmond, 29 Jan. 1781. Minute in the War Office Journal (Vi) under this date: Letter, to the Governor respecting the issuing spirits to the Officers and Soldiers in the State Service, and an order enclosed for a hogshead of rum to be delivered Francis Graves, to be issued to the Officers, Soldiers, tradesmen &c. if he approves of it. Muters letter and its enclosure have not been located. TJs reply is dated 31 Jan. 1781, q.v.]
